Name: Hhohho
Description: Hhohho is located in the northern part of Eswatini and is home to the country s capital, Mbabane. It is known for its natural beauty, including mountains and forests.

Name: Lubombo
Description: Lubombo is located in the eastern part of Eswatini and is known for its proximity to the Kruger National Park in South Africa. It has a diverse agricultural sector.

Name: Manzini
Description: Manzini is the central region of Eswatini and serves as the commercial hub of the country. It has a well-developed infrastructure and is important for trade and commerce.

Name: Shiselweni
Description: Shiselweni is located in the southern part of Eswatini and is known for its agriculture, particularly sugarcane farming. It also has some mining activities.
